      "description": "Offering a driver-focused 996.2 Carrera featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus. This unit delivers a linear power band paired with a precise G96 six-speed manual transaxle. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh Rear Main Seal (RMS). The suspension retains its factory composure with MacPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup, providing excellent lateral stability. The braking system features four-piston monobloc calipers and vented rotors for consistent thermal dissipation. While the exterior shows honest patina from enthusiast use, the mechanical drivetrain remains tight with no vacuum leaks or bore scoring symptoms. A mechanically sorted example ready for the canyons.",
